AS 44.64.010
) not later than seven days after the effective date of the order prohibiting the physician from practicing. The board may lift an order prohibiting a physician from practicing if the board finds after a hearing that the physician is able to practice with reasonable skill and safety. The physician may appeal a decision of the board under this subsection to the superior court.

